divs: Sighting DetailsEast London, United Kingdom Low in the sky looking towards Canary Wharf Object approximately on the left side of Canary wharf towers (viewed from All Saints DLR station), object relatively low in the sky. Object has not moved for more than an hour, noticed it around 00:30 hours. Not an airline, no sound and the object has not moved at all for more than an hour. Bright light in the center is clearly visible, vague disc shaped outline with bright light in the centre surrounded by 6 small lights. No sound. Date: June 10 2008 Time zone: GMT Approximate time of first observation: 00:30 AM Location, London (East London, looking towards Canary Wharf from All Saints DLR station, visible on the left side of Canary Wharf towers, relatively low in the sky). Approximate time of last observation: 01:50 AM Stars clearly visible in the background. Tried to take a picture with camera on the cell phone, cannot focus on the object, cell phone camera just shows a black screen.
Summary: Disc with bright light in the centre, small lights around, stationery for 1 hour+
trends: There have been 91 other sightings in London
